Q1. Why do we call Python as a general purpose and high-level programming language?
A)Since python is designed to be used for building software in a wide variety of application domains,and also it is 
in human readable format it is called high- level programming language.

Q2. Why is Python called a dynamically typed language?
A)Since its type of the variable is determined during runtime not at compile time.

Q3. List some pros and cons of Python programming language?
A) pros---> general purpose language , easy to learn compared other languages, object-oreinted
   cons---> slower than compiled languages like c++, high memory consuption 

Q4. In what all domains can we use Python?
A)it can be used in ML, AI , Data science, Web devolopment,Gaming and many more

Q5. What are variable and how can we declare them?
A)varibales are nothing name given to a address to access them .It has no command for declaring a variable. A variable is created the moment you first assign a value to it.

Q6. How can we take an input from the user in Python?
A)using input() function

Q7. What is the default datatype of the value that has been taken as an input using input() function?
A)String

Q8. What is type casting?
A)converting one data type to other.

Q9. Can we take more than one input from the user using single input() function? If yes, how? If no, why?
A) yes it can be done with combination of split() method which uses a seperator(optional).

Q10. What are keywords?
A)Python keywords are special reserved words that have specific meanings and purposes and can't be used for anything but those specific purposes.

Q11. Can we use keywords as a variable? Support your answer with reason.
A)no keywords cant be used as variable because it has some meaning predefined and python doesnt know whether it is a keyword or
variable if we use variable as keyword.

Q12. What is indentation? What's the use of indentaion in Python?
A)Indentation refers to the spaces at the beginning of a code line. Python uses indentation to indicate a block of code.

Q13. How can we throw some output in Python?
A)using print() 

Q14. What are operators in Python?
A)operators are special symbols that designate that some sort of computation should be performed. such as addition,sub,etc

Q15. What is difference between / and // operators?
A)/ is for floating div and // is for integer div

